dict.string: Vegetables and Salad Greens (fresh, canned or frozen)
Tomatoes, fresh and canned: round, plum, cherry
Beans: azuki, chickpeas, garbanzo beans, black, butter, cannellini, kidney,lima, navy, pinto or white
Chicken: boneless, skinless dark or white meat, ground
Salmon: fresh, frozen, or nitrate-free smoked
Jerky, nitrate-free: buffalo, turkey, elk, ostrich
Tuna, fresh or packed in water or oil
Broths, Herbs, Spices, Condiments, and Supplements
Ketchup: no sugar added, no corn syrup
Natural seasonings: Bragg Liquid Aminos, coconut amino acids

Seasonings: black and white peppers, celery seed, chophouse seasoning, cinnamon, chili powder, crushed red pepper flakes, cumin, curry powder, onion salt, paprika, raw cacao powder, turmeric, sea salt, Simply Organic seasoning
Tomato paste, tomato sauce; no sugar added
All broths should be free of additives and preservatives.
Coconut: coconut butter, coconut milk, coconut cream, coconut water
Nuts nut/seed butters and pastes, raw: almonds, cashews, hazelnuts, pecans, pine nuts, pistachios, walnuts
Oils: coconut, grapeseed, olive, sesame, toasted sesame (Asian) seeds
Raw: flax, hemp, pumpkin, sesame, sunflower, tahini
